
1. switches runs a code if its case equates the given expression.

2. break; is used to exit switch, if break is not used in a case, then switch will run all cases till end.

3. switch case comparison is strict, even data type should also match with the value for a case to run

4. In while loop condition is checked before loop body is executed.

while(condition){ code }

5. In do while, loop body is executed first, then condition is checked.

do { code   } 
while(condition)

